<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO LUCIEN LOMBARDO</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb 18  0:52:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I hope your coverage of Vietnam isn't limited to My Lai.  As an officer in Vietnam; I knew what was and what wasn't a lawful order.  Many of us would never have participated in or condoned such a thing.  Several million Americans passed through Vietnam, and most did not take part in an atrocities.  Every time I go into a high school to speak about the war, I have to overcome the idea that we are/were crazed druggies.  A military is supposed to be able to deal in the controlled application of violence when necessary.  My Lai was neither controlled or necessary.<br>
     
<p><code>-- turtle@plantaganet.com  (Gerald Ney, &quot;the Herd&quot; 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


